# Core Rules

- Make the smallest safe change that solves the request.
- Do not rewrite unrelated code.
- Before editing, inspect the relevant existing files.
- Prefer simple, boring, maintainable solutions over clever abstractions.
- Preserve existing architecture, naming, formatting, and public APIs unless explicitly asked.
- When uncertain, state the assumption briefly and continue with the safest reasonable implementation.
- Do not add new dependencies unless necessary. Explain why before adding one.
- Never remove tests, validation, error handling, logging, auth checks, or security checks to make code pass.